  "title": "Staff Nurse/ Senior Staff Nurse (Interventional Radiology)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Provide radiology and perioperative nursing care.</li><li>Assist radiologist and surgeons during radiological procedures and operations.</li><li>Monitor and assess patient pre, intra and post procedures</li><li>Coordinate and collaborate with multi-disciplinary caregivers in providing safe efficient patient care. </li><li>Prepare patient for MRI procedure and cannulation for scan.</li><li>Recover patient after day surgery operation.</li><li>Follow up with specimen result and charges.</li><li>Guide and train new nurses.</li><li>Maintain good inventory of medication and stock</li><li>Prepare and organize for next day cases</li><li>Demonstrate proper use, care and maintenance of equipment and supplies.</li><li>Demonstrate proper and economical usage of sterile supplies and consumables.</li><li>Assist in inventories and equipment maintenance.</li><li>Ensure adequate daily supplies of consumables.</li><li>Assist with optimal OT room utilization</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Registered Nurse with Singapore Nursing Board </li><li>BCLS & AED Certified</li><li>Diploma or degree in nursing or equivalent</li><li>At least 1 or 2 years' experience as a Staff Nurse in a clinical setting</li></ul><p></p>",
